did.abstract: The collection consists of inactive records from the University at Albany's Office of Accounting.
did.physloc: The materials are located onsite in the department.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to this collection is unrestricted.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: All items in this manuscript group were transferred to the University Libraries, M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives.

arrangement.head: Arrangement of the Collection
arrangement.p: Physical items in the collection were maintained in the original order after transfer.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: The University at Albany's Office of Accounting establishes policies and procedures associated with the University's fiscal transactions. The Office publishes guidelines for University employees on the use of university funds and offers guidance on travel reimbursement.

phystech.head: Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements
phystech.p: Web Archives

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Preferred citation for this material is as follows:

Identification of specific item, series, box, folder, Office of Accounting Records. M.E. Grenander Department of Special Collections and Archives, University Libraries, University at Albany, State University of New York (hereafter referred to as the Office of Accounting Records).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of departmental accounting and expense reports, memoranda on claims and billing procedures, manuals for travel procedure, reports and memoranda from the Office of Sponsored Funds, and the annual Chart of Accounts, 1971-1980. The collection also contains web-captures of the Office of Accounting's website from 2004 to the present.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Collection was maintained in the original order after it was transferred.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of departmental accounting reports, memoranda on claims and billing procedures, departmental expense reports, manuals for travel procedure, reports and memoranda from the Office of Sponsored Funds, and the annual Chart of Accounts, 1971-1980.
The collections consists of memoranda on accounting practices, 1970-83, the Office of Sponsored Funds, 1975-82, progress reports on Sponsored Funds, 1967-69, and a chart of accounts, 1971-80.
